<LI>Supplementary material
<P><A HREF="jurman07algebraicRev1-suppmat.pdf">PDF</a> (334 K)</P></LI>
<LI>Software</LI>
<P><B>ListsPy</B> is a Python application with a Tk GUI, for *nix and Windows systems. It runs by using a C library (faster) or, if the library version is not compatible, as a plain Python application. The included C library is compiled for a 32bit system as a Linux (RHEL4) shared object and as a Windows DLL; for different systems, a Makefile is provided.
<P>The package is available via SVN: <pre>svn co http://biodcv.itc.it/svn/ListsPy/trunk</pre></P>
<P>Or, you can download the latest build: <A HREF="ListsPy-20080527_1032.tgz">ListsPy-20080527_1032.tgz</A> (175 Kb)</P>

<P>
The software requires a few Python packages, but has been written with portability in mind.<br>
We have tested it under the following configurations:
</P>
